    "Larger images are slower to process but may capture more details or features that are helpful for object detection.",
    "Therefore, choosing an appropriate image size is a trade-off between speed and accuracy.",
    "Currently, we have trained our model with only 2000 annotated images of the TMC-2 sensor from the Chadrayaan-2 satellite 30.",
    "Further, in extended work, we strive to find an acceptable balance between processing efficiency and detection precision by carefully selecting image sizes.",
    "We also intend to use ArcGIS Pro with DEM images to improve crater detection accuracy."
